# Law on webscraping -
the law favors web scraping data as long as we think about couple of things
1) Data that is publicly available and not copyrighted, then it's legal,
2) If we are using for our own purposes, then it's okay, but if we are commercializing that data
when we set up a business and needs that data, that's grey area.

# We can't commercialise copyrighted data on our own website.
# You can't scrape the data behind the authentication
# The data not behind the authentication can't be bound to a policy.

# A lot of websites use captcha and recaptcha to prevent web scraping to prevent
bots like our python code from accessing the website


